Detailed Description

This head file contains internal identifiers, which are those shared between the files of the driver. It is intended for internal use only.

                     as they were wrongly defined

 10.0  bss  6/24/14  Removed support for families older than 7 series.
		      Removed IDCODE macros.

Value:
(Block << XHI_FAR_BLOCK_SHIFT) | \
        ((Top << XHI_FAR_TOP_BOTTOM_SHIFT) | \
        (Row << XHI_FAR_ROW_ADDR_SHIFT) | \
        (ColumnAddress << XHI_FAR_COLUMN_ADDR_SHIFT) | \
        (MinorAddress << XHI_FAR_MINOR_ADDR_SHIFT))

Generates a Type 1 packet header that is written to the Frame Address Register (FAR) for a Virtex5 device.

Parameters:
Block - Address Block Type (CLB or BRAM address space)
Top - top (0) or bottom (1) half of device
Row - Row Address
ColumnAddress - CLB or BRAM column
MinorAddress - Frame within a column
Returns:
Type 1 packet header to write the FAR
Note:
None.
